[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpsqkfplm9[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTikaAppUntarringFuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA file path traversal vulnerability was detected in Apache Tika's untarring [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality during fuzzing with the TikaAppUntarringFuzzer. The vulnerability [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallows directory traversal through specially crafted tar archive entries, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpotentially enabling an attacker to write files outside the intended extraction [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Vulnerability Type[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis is a **File Path Traversal** [0m[1;39m([0m[39malso known as Directory Traversal or Path [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTraversal[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vulnerability, as explicitly identified by the Jazzer security [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer: `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal`.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### What the Issue Is[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzing process detected that when processing a tar archive, the [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTikaAppUntarringFuzzer attempts to extract files to paths that traverse outside the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdesignated extraction directory. Specifically, the vulnerability manifests when the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode tries to create or access the path [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/tmp/expander-tmp12131473402931060068/output/q/r/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`. The Jazzer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity hooks intercepted this attempted path traversal operation and raised a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritical security exception.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations and Findings[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Detection Point**: The vulnerability was caught by Jazzer's FilePathTraversal [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer hooks at runtime, specifically in the method chain:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mFilePathTraversal.check[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mFilePathTraversal.checkPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo fully understand this vulnerability, the following codebase components should be[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Primary Location**: [0m                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Path Handling Logic**:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How `TikaUntar` processes tar archive entries and constructs output file paths[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.tar.TarArchiveEntry` - How entry paths [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare extracted and normalized[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `org.apache.commons.io.FileUtils` and `org.apache.commons.io.file.PathUtils` -[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFile and path manipulation utilities that may propagate unsafe paths[0m                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Security Controls**:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing path validation or normalization functions[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Checks for relative path components [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m[32m"../"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in archive entry names[0m       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m52[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mexpected.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"testPPT.ppt"[0m[39m, 16384l[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m53[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mexpected.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"testPDF.pdf"[0m[39m, 34824l[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m54[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mexpected.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"testHTML.html"[0m[39m, 167l[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m55[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mexpected.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"testWORD.doc"[0m[39m, 19456l[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m56[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mexpected.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"testRTF.rtf"[0m[39m, 3410l[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m57[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mexpected.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"testOpenOffice2.odt"[0m[39m, 26448l[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mexpected.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"testTXT.txt"[0m[39m, 49l[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mexpected.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"testEXCEL.xls"[0m[39m, 13824l[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mexpected.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"testXML.xml"[0m[39m, 766l[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35massertTrue[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mFiles.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractDir[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m:        Path testDocuments = [0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"test-documents"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35massertTrue[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mFiles.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtestDocuments[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:        int found = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m:        for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mFile f : [0m[1;35mtestDocuments.toFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.listFiles[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m69[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35massertEquals[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mf.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mexpected.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mf.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m:            found++;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35massertEquals[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mexpected.size[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, found[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m73[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m74[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m75[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy for Path Traversal Vulnerability in TikaUntar.java[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability exists in [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-app/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/cli/TikaUntar.java` at lines [0m[1;36m43[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m47[0m[39m. The [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPath target = [0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mFiles.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mFiles.createDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mFiles.write[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtarget, [0m[1;35mtais.readAllBytes[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**The Problem:**[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m43[0m[39m resolves the tar entry name against the extraction directory and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormalizes it[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- However, it **does not validate** that the normalized path remains within [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`extractDir`[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A malicious tar entry like `[0m[32m"../../../etc/passwd"[0m[39m` can escape the extraction [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method only removes `.` and `..` syntactically but doesn't [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidate the result stays within bounds[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After normalization, a path like `[0m[35m/tmp/extract/../../../tmp/[0m[95mevil.txt[0m[39m` becomes [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/tmp/[0m[95mevil.txt[0m[39m`, which is outside the extraction directory[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Fix Implementation Steps[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Add null byte validation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefense in depth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBefore processing the entry name, add a check for null byte injection following the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern used in `FileSystemFetcher.java`:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.contains[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"\u0000"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid entry name contains null byte: "[0m[39m + [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Add path traversal validation**[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter creating parent directories but before writing the file, validate that the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolved path stays within the extraction directory. The validation must use [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to resolve symbolic links and get the canonical path:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Create parent directories first [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrequired for toRealPath validation[0m[1;39m)[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mFiles.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mFiles.createDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Security: Validate path doesn't escape extraction directory[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mextractDir.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Entry is outside of the target dir: "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Complete patched code for lines [0m[1;36m41[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m50[0m[39m:**[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtae != null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.isFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Security: Check for null byte injection[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.contains[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"\u0000"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid entry name contains null byte: "[0m[39m + [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        Path target = [0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Create parent directories first [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrequired for toRealPath validation[0m[1;39m)[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mFiles.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mFiles.createDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Security: Validate path doesn't escape extraction directory[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Use [0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to resolve symbolic links and get canonical path[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mextractDir.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Entry is outside of the target dir: "[0m[39m + [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mFiles.write[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtarget, [0m[1;35mtais.readAllBytes[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    tae = [0m[1;35mtais.getNextEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why this is the optimal approach:**[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Follows established Tika patterns**: The fix uses the same security pattern [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malready implemented in `FileSystemFetcher.java` lines [0m[1;36m71[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m82[0m[39m, which validates paths [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39musing `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Uses [0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for maximum security**: Unlike `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Resolves symbolic links to their actual targets [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprevents symlink-based [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattacks[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Normalizes the path [0m[1;39m([0m[39mremoves `.` and `..` components[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Converts to an absolute canonical path[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Provides the strongest guarantee that the path is within the extraction [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Validates at the right time**: The validation occurs after creating parent [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectories [0m[1;39m([0m[39mso `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` succeeds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but before writing the file [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpreventing [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexploitation[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Validates the parent directory**: We validate [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` because:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The target file doesn't exist yet [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwill be created by `[0m[1;35mFiles.write[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The parent directory exists after `[0m[1;35mcreateDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The filename component alone cannot cause directory traversal[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach is sufficient and practical[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**How it preserves existing functionality:**[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Maintains directory structure**: The fix still allows legitimate paths like [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[32m"test-documents/testPDF.pdf"[0m[39m` to create subdirectories, which is required by [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TikaUntarTest.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m65[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Doesn't break existing tests**: The test expects files under [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`extractDir/test-documents/`, and the fix preserves this behavior while blocking [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalicious traversal.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Same I/O patterns**: The fix adds validation but doesn't change the file [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcreation logic, so all legitimate use cases continue to work.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**How it addresses the security issue:**[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Blocks path traversal**: Paths like `[0m[32m"../../../etc/passwd"[0m[39m` will fail the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation because the resolved real path won't start with [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mextractDir.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Prevents symlink attacks**: Using `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` resolves symbolic links, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreventing attackers from using symlinks to escape the extraction directory.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Defense in depth**: The null byte check prevents another class of path [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minjection attacks.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Clear error messages**: When an attack is detected, the exception includes the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry name for debugging and security logging.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Potential side effects and mitigations:**[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **IOException from [0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: If the parent directory doesn't exist or [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthere are permission issues, `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` will throw an exception. This is [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmitigated because we create the parent directories first [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m44[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m45[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Performance impact**: Calling `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` on every entry has minimal [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mperformance impact compared to the I/O operations of extracting files. The security[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbenefit far outweighs the negligible performance cost.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Platform-specific path handling**: `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` handles platform-specific [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths correctly [0m[1;39m([0m[39mWindows, Unix, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so the fix works across platforms.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Similar solutions in the codebase:**[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis fix directly mirrors the security pattern in:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `FileSystemFetcher.java` lines [0m[1;36m78[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m82[0m[39m: Uses `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for path [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `FileSystemFetcher.java` lines [0m[1;36m71[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m74[0m[39m: Checks for null bytes in paths[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe Tika developers have already identified and implemented this pattern elsewhere [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the codebase, confirming it's the correct approach for Tika's security model.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintended extraction directory [0m[1;39m([0m[39mspecifically, a path containing [0m[32m"jazzer-traversal"[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min a deep directory structure[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A patch was attempted to address this vulnerability[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby adding null byte validation and path traversal checks before file extraction. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHowever, the patch introduced a new runtime error: a `NoSuchFileException` caused [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby calling `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` on a parent directory that doesn't yet exist, preventing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe successful execution of the fuzzer test.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer execution revealed a critical security issue:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== Java Exception: com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFile path traversal: [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/expander-tmp12131473402931060068/output/q/r/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis exception was triggered by the `FilePathTraversal` sanitizer hook at line [0m[1;36m346[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich detected an attempt to create a file outside the intended extraction [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory. The call stack shows:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The sanitizer hook intercepted the path creation at [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FilePathTraversal.pathFirstArgHook`[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. This occurred during `TikaUntar.main` execution at line [0m[1;36m47[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The fuzzer invoked this through `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer.parseOne` method[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability exists in the tar extraction logic where files from a tar archive[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan be extracted to arbitrary paths, potentially allowing malicious archives to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite files outside the intended extraction directory. The fuzzer successfully [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentified this with a test case that generated paths like [0m[32m"q/r/jazzer-traversal"[0m[39m.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modified `tika-app/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/cli/TikaUntar.java` by [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madding security checks:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Null Byte Validation**: Added a check to reject entry names containing null [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`\u0000`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.contains[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"\u0000"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid entry name contains null byte: "[0m[39m + [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Path Normalization**: The existing code already normalized the target path, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut the patch made this more explicit.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Path Traversal Prevention**: Added a check to verify that the extracted file's[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparent directory, when resolved to its real path, remains within the extraction [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mextractDir.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Entry is outside of the target dir: "[0m[39m + [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Post-Patch Results[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the fuzzer encountered a different error:[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCaused by: java.nio.file.NoSuchFileException: [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/expander-tmp18298167691066694426/output/q/r/s/[0m[95mt[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat java.base/[0m[1;35msun.nio.fs.UnixPath.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUnixPath.jav[0m[1;92ma:825[0m[1;39m)[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar.main[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaUntar.jav[0m[1;92ma:53[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe exception occurs at line [0m[1;36m53[0m[39m, which corresponds to the newly added path [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal check. The issue is that `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` requires the path to exist in the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfilesystem, but at the time of the check:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The parent directory structure [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`q/r/s/t`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m has been created by the [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mFiles.createDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call at lines [0m[1;36m49[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m51[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- However, calling `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` on a path that exists but may contain symbolic [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlinks or other filesystem complexities causes the `NoSuchFileException`[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis indicates that while the patch correctly attempted to prevent path traversal, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe implementation has a logic error: it's trying to resolve the real path of a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory that has just been created programmatically and may not be fully realized[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the filesystem at the time of the check.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Further Investigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **TikaUntar.java**: The core extraction logic needs review to understand:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The complete flow of tar entry processing[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How directory creation is handled before file extraction[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The relationship between normalized paths and real paths in the context of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnewly created directories[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Path Resolution Timing**: Investigation needed into:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` can be safely called on newly created directories[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether the check should occur before or after directory creation[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Alternative methods for validating paths that don't require filesystem [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolution[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Test Coverage**: The fuzzer test case that triggers this issue should be [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexamined to understand:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The specific tar archive structure being tested[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sequence of entries in the archive [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdirectories vs. files[0m[1;39m)[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether the issue is related to deep directory nesting or specific path [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatterns[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Security Model**: A broader analysis is needed of:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How Apache Tika intends to handle untrusted archives[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - What the expected behavior should be for archives with unusual path structures[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether the current approach of allowing arbitrary directory creation is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfundamentally sound[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[33mFUZZER[0m[39m=[0m[35mTikaAppUntarringFuzzer[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
