[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Updated Analysis[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter reviewing the test, I see that:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m65[0m[39m**: The test expects a `test-documents` subdirectory to exist in the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutput[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m68[0m[39m**: Files are looked for inside `testDocuments` directory, not directly[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `extractDir`[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. This means tar entries are like `test-documents/testPPT.ppt`, and the directory [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure MUST be preserved[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMy previous approach of using `[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` would strip the directory [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponent and break this test. I need a different strategy that:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Validates that the resolved path is within the target directory[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Preserves legitimate directory structures[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Only blocks actual path traversal attempts[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Revised Fix Strategy[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe correct approach is to:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Keep the path resolution logic** - Use [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to get the full target path[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Validate the resolved path** - Check that it's within extractDir boundaries[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Skip malicious entries** - Log and continue when path traversal is detected[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Wrap in try-catch** - Handle IO errors gracefully[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis is actually closer to the failed patch, but instead of throwing IOException, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwe skip the entry.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Implementation Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Add imports:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   import org.slf4j.Logger;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Add logger field:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   private static final Logger LOG = [0m[1;35mLoggerFactory.getLogger[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaUntar.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Modify the entry processing logic:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtae != null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.isFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Check for null bytes[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.contains[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"\u0000"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Skipping entry with null byte in name: "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               tae = [0m[1;35mtais.getNextEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               continue;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               Path target = [0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Validate path is within extractDir[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               if [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mextractDir.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normal[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Skipping entry outside target directory: "[0m[39m + [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   tae = [0m[1;35mtais.getNextEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   continue;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mFiles.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   [0m[1;35mFiles.createDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[1;35mFiles.write[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtarget, [0m[1;35mtais.readAllBytes[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Failed to extract entry: "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[32m" - "[0m[39m + [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35me.getMessage[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       tae = [0m[1;35mtais.getNextEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why this is the optimal approach:**[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Preserves directory structure**: For legitimate entries like [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`test-documents/testPPT.ppt`, the path is resolved correctly and the directory [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure is maintained [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtest requirement from lines [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m65[0m[1;39m)[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Blocks path traversal**: For malicious entries like `..[0m[35m/../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe validation detects the traversal and skips the entry with a warning[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **No exceptions thrown to caller**: The try-catch catches IO errors during [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction, and path traversal is handled with continue statements, so the main [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod completes successfully[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Follows Tika patterns**: [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - TikaCLI.parseEmbedded [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1118[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1124[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m wraps operations in try-catch and logs[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwarnings[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - FileSystemFetcher.isDescendant [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m67[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m provides the same validation [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - PackageParser [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m492[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m495[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m508[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m510[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m records errors and continues processing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Addresses security issue**: The path traversal check prevents the Jazzer [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFilePathTraversal hook from triggering because malicious paths are never passed to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mFiles.write[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**How it preserves existing logic:**[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The resolution logic `[0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` remains the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Directory creation works correctly for legitimate paths[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- File writing works correctly for legitimate entries[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The loop continues processing all entries[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**How it addresses the evaluation report issues:**[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Initial issue**: Path traversal prevented by validation check before file [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwriting[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Post-patch issue**: No IOException thrown; instead, malicious entries are [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mskipped with logging, and fuzzer completes successfully[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Differences from failed patch:**[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m| Failed Patch | Revised Strategy |[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m|--------------|------------------|[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m| Throws IOException for path traversal | Logs warning and continues |[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m| Crashes fuzzer with exit code [0m[1;36m77[0m[39m | Completes successfully with exit code [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m |[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m| Same validation logic | Same validation logic |[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Potential side effects and mitigation:**[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Side effect**: Malicious entries are silently skipped [0m[1;39m([0m[39monly logged[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: This is intentional - batch processing should be resilient. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe warning log provides visibility for debugging.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Side effect**: IO errors during extraction don't fail the entire operation[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: This matches TikaCLI behavior and is appropriate for CLI [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mutilities processing multiple files[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Side effect**: [0m[3;35mNone[0m[39m - the test will pass because legitimate entries are [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessed normally[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Referenced similar solutions:**[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- FileSystemFetcher [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m67[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m79[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m82[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Uses the same `[0m[1;35mstartsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` validation [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- TikaCLI.parseEmbedded [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1118[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1124[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Uses the same try-catch and log pattern[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- PackageParser [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m492[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m495[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Shows the pattern of recording errors and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinuing[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis solution is optimal because it combines proven validation logic from [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFileSystemFetcher with proven error handling from TikaCLI, adapted appropriately [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor the TikaUntar use case.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                   [0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.END                      ]8;id=657237;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=720316;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\

[2;36m                    [0m         [95moutput-1767887122.2589514[0m                                                            [2m               [0m

[2;36m[01/08/26 15:45:24][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Deleting environments directory: [35m/home/user/crete/.cache/environments/[0m[95mtika[0m           ]8;id=114065;file:///home/user/crete/scripts/benchmark/__main__.py\[2m__main__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=216262;file:///home/user/crete/scripts/benchmark/__main__.py#300\[2m300[0m]8;;\

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mtika[0m                   [2m               [0m
